      "text": "function test_fish_lsp --argument-names file --description \"Check a file for syntax errors\"\n    echo \"$file\"\n    lso\n    fzf-local-node_modules\nend\n\n## this is a comment\nfunction __test_small\n    if string match --regex '^(\\w{10}).fish' -- \"$argv\"\n        echo matched | string pad -c ' '\n    end\n    string match --regex '[[:alnum:]]' \"$argv\"\n\n    # padding a stirng\n    string pad --char \" \" \"$argv\"\n    set_color --background black white\n    set -l variable_name \"v a\"\n    whatis -? --config-file --help --regex \"*\"\n    set -l variable_name (string split0 --fields 1 --right --max 4 '\\t' \"$argv\")\n    string pad --width 10 --char \" \" \"$argv\"\n    set -l variable_name \"value u\"\n    if test -n \"$variable_name\"\n        echo \"$variable_name is not empty\"\n    end\n\n    for i in $variable_name\n        echo $i\n    end\n\n\nend\n\nset -l file \"$argv\"\ntest_fish_lsp $file\n"
    }
  }
}

      "text": "function test_fish_lsp --argument-names file --description \"Check a file for syntax errors\"\n    echo \"$file\"\n    lso\n    fzf-local-node_modules\nend\n\n## this is a comment\nfunction __test_small\n    if string match --regex '^(\\w{10}).fish' -- \"$argv\"\n        echo matched | string pad -c ' '\n    end\n    string match --regex '[[:alnum:]]' \"$argv\"\n\n    # padding a stirng\n    string pad --char \" \" \"$argv\"\n    set_color --background black white\n    set -l variable_name \"v a\"\n    whatis -? --config-file --help --regex \"*\"\n    set -l variable_name (string split0 --fields 1 --right --max 4 '\\t' \"$argv\")\n    string pad --width 10 --char \" \" \"$argv\"\n    set -l variable_name \"value u\"\n    if test -n \"$variable_name\"\n        echo \"$variable_name is not empty\"\n    end\n\n    for i in $variable_name\n        echo $i\n    end\n\n\nend\n\nset -l file \"$argv\"\ntest_fish_lsp $file\n"

      "text": "function test_fish_lsp --argument-names file --description \"Check a file for syntax errors\"\n    echo \"$file\"\n    lso\n    fzf-local-node_modules\nend\n\n## this is a comment\nfunction __test_small\n    if string match --regex '^(\\w{10}).fish' -- \"$argv\"\n        echo matched | string pad -c ' '\n    end\n    string match --regex '[[:alnum:]]' \"$argv\"\n\n    # padding a stirng\n    string pad --char \" \" \"$argv\"\n    set_color --background black white\n    set -l variable_name \"v a\"\n    whatis -? --config-file --help --regex \"*\"\n    set -l variable_name (string split0 --fields 1 --right --max 4 '\\t' \"$argv\")\n    string pad --width 10 --char \" \" \"$argv\"\n    set -l variable_name \"value u\"\n    if test -n \"$variable_name\"\n        echo \"$variable_name is not empty\"\n    end\n\n    for i in $variable_name\n        echo $i\n    end\n\n\nend\n\nset -l file \"$argv\"\ntest_fish_lsp $file\n"

      "languageId": "fish",
      "version": 1,
      "text": "function jump_location --argument-names location\n    switch \"$location\"\n        case f\n            if test \"$PWD\" = \"$FISH_PATH\"\n                cd $FUNCTIONS_PATH\n            else\n                cd $FISH_PATH\n            end\n        case c\n            \n    end\n\nend\n\n\nfunction __jump_f\n    switch \"$PWD\"\n        case $FISH_PATH\n            cd $FUNCTIONS_PATH\n        case \"*\"\n            cd $FISH_PATH\n    end\nend\n\nfunction __jump_c\n    switch \"$PWD\"\n        case $FISH_PATH\n            cd $FISH_PATH/completions\n        case \"*\"\n            cd $HOME/.config/\n    end\nend\n\n\nfunction __jump_s\n    switch \"$PWD\"\n        case $FISH_PATH\n            cd $FISH_PATH/conf.d\n        case \"*\"\n            cd $HOME/.config/fish/\n    end\nend\n"
    }
  }

      "text": "function jump_location --argument-names location\n    switch \"$location\"\n        case f\n            __jump_f\n        case c\n            __jump_c\n        case r\n            gt r\n        case ws_3\n            __jump_ws_3\n    end\n    commandline -f repaint\nend\n\n\nfunction __jump_f\n    switch \"$PWD\"\n        case $FISH_PATH\n            cd $FUNCTIONS_PATH\n        case \"*\"\n            cd $FISH_PATH\n            set -a dirnext $FISH_PATH/functions\n    end\nend\n\nfunction __jump_c\n    switch \"$PWD\"\n        case $FISH_PATH\n            cd $FISH_PATH/completions\n        case \"*\"\n            cd $HOME/.config/\n    end\nend\n\n\nfunction __jump_s\n    cd $HOME/.config/fish/\nend\n\n\nfunction __jump_ws_3\n    cd $workspace_3\n    set -l dirnext\n    if test -d $workspace_3/src/utils\n        set -a dirnext $workspace_3/src/utils\n    end\n    if test -d $workspace_3/src\n        set -a dirnext $workspace_3/src\n    end\n    set -gx dirnext $dirnext\nend\n"
    }

$HOME/School\nset course_path $school_path/School\nset projects_path $HOME/Projects\nset org_path $HOME/Dropbox/org\n\nfunction gt -d 'go to directory in $PATH'\n    if test -z $argv\n        __goto_default;\n        return 0;\n    else if test -d $argv\n        cd $argv;\n        return 0;\n    else if string match -raq \"(--|-)?u(\\d)?\" -- \"$argv\";\n        __up_directories $argv;\n        return 0;\n    end\n\n    set -l args (args_regex_helper $argv | string lower)\n    switch \"$args\"\n        case \"n\" \"nvim\"\n            cd $nvim_path;\n            return 0;\n        case cd $course_path/cs445;\n            return 0;\n        case \"math\"\n            cd $course_path/Math;\n            return 0;\n        case 'coc'\n            cd $config_path/coc;\n            return $HOME/.mozilla/firefox\n            firefox \"about:profiles\"\n            return 0\n        case \\*\n            __gt_err_msg\n            return 1\n    end\nend\n\nfunction __gt_root_project\n    set -l rootProjectDir (upfind -name '.git');\n    if test -d $rootProjectDir\n        cd $rootProjectDir\n    else\n        set_color magenta;echo \"Uh oh, error finding root project directory\";\n        return;\n    end\nend\n\nfunction __gt_frontend\n    set -l rootProjectDir (upfind -name '.git');\n    if test -d $rootProjectDir/frontend\n        cd $rootProjectDir/frontend\n    else\n        set_color magenta;echo \"Uh oh, error finding root project directory\";\n        return;\n    end\nend\n\nfunction __gt_backend\n    set -l rootProjectDir (upfind -name '.git');\n    if test -d $rootProjectDir/backend\n        cd $rootProjectDir/backend\n    else\n        set_color magenta;echo \"Uh oh, error finding root project directory\";\n        return;\n    end\nend\n\nfunction __gt_down_project\n    set -l rootProjectDir (upfind -name '.git');\n    if test -d $rootProjectDir\n        set -l found (fd --base-directory \"$rootProjectDir\" \"$argv\" -a)\n        if test -d $found \n            cd $found\n        else\n            set_color magenta;echo \"Uh oh, error finding $argv directory\";\n        end\n    else\n        set_color magenta;echo \"Uh oh, error finding root project directory\";\n        return;\n    end \nend\n\nfunction __goto_default \n    set -l default_goto_dir (usr_cat $fish_path/gt_default)\n    cd $default_goto_dir;\nend\n\nfunction __set_default\n    pwd > ~/.config/fish/gt_default;\nend\n\nfunction __up_directories\n    set -l current_path $PWD;\n    set -l path_array (string split \"/\" \"$current_path\")\n    set -l path_sz (count $path_array)\n\n    set -l up_amount 1\n    set -l up_arg_amount (echo \"$argv\" | string trim -c '-u')\n    if not test -z \"$up_arg_amount\";\n        set up_amount $up_arg_amount\n    end;\n    \n    if test $up_amount -ge $path_sz;\n        set_random_color --error --background --reset --command='echo -n \"WARNING\"'\n        set_random_color --error --command=\"echo -n 'up amount flag [$up_amount]' >= size of path [$path_sz]\"\n        set -l up_amount $path_sz;\n    end;\n\n    for i in (seq 1 $up_amount);\n        cd ../;\n    end;\n    return;\nend\n\nfunction __gt_err_msg\n    set -l str_arg (echo \"\")\n    if not test -z $argv\n        set -l str_arg (echo $argv)\n    end\n    if test $str_arg = \"\"\n        set_color magenta;echo \"Uh oh, error in FISH Go To Function\"; echo \"\";\n        set_random_color -b; echo \"To edit the Fish Go To Function, use the command below:\";\n        set_random_color -b -B --command='echo -e \\'gt e'\\';\n    else if test $str_arg = \"0\" \n        set_color magenta; echo \"Uh oh, error in FISH Go To Function\"; echo \"\";\n        set_random_color -b; echo \"To edit the Fish Go To Function, use the command below:\";\n        set_random_color -b -B --command='echo -e \\'gt e'\\';\n    else if test $str_arg = \"1\"\n        set_color magenta; echo \"Uh oh, nothing was passed to Find Go To\";\n    else if test $str_arg = \"root\" -o $str_arg = \"2\"\n        set_color magenta;echo \"Uh oh, error finding root project directory\";\n    else if test $str_arg = \"2\"\n        set_color magenta;echo \"Uh oh, error finding $argv directory\";\n    else \n        set_color magenta;echo \"nothing found\";\n    end\n    set_color_normal;\nend\n"
    }

      "version": 1,
      "text": "function jump_location --argument-names location\n    switch \"$location\"\n        case f\n            __jump_f\n        case c\n            __jump_c\n        case r\n            gt r\n        case ws_3\n            __jump_ws_3\n        case ts\n            cd $tsplayground\n    end\n    commandline -f repaint\nend\n\n\n#set -l parent_pwd (upfind -name fish)\nfunction __jump_f\n    switch \"$PWD\"\n        case $FISH_PATH\n            cd $FISH_PATH/functions\n            set -gx dirnext $FISH_PATH/completions $FISH_PATH/scripts\n        case \"*\"\n            cd $FISH_PATH\n            set -gx dirnext $FISH_PATH/completions $FISH_PATH/scripts $FISH_PATH/functions \n    end\nend\n\nfunction __jump_c\n    cd $HOME/.config/\n    set -gx dirnext $FISH_PATH $NVIM_PATH\nend\n\n\n# EXE is path variable name for $FISH_PATH/scripts\nfunction __jump_s\n    cd $EXE\nend\n\n\n# @see ../config.fish [line : 39 ]\nfunction __jump_ws_3\n    cd $workspace_3\n    #set -gx dirnext (echo (fd --type d -a --changed-within 1week)[-1..1] | string split ' ')[-3..-1]\n    if test -d $workspace_3/src/utils\n        set -a dirnext $workspace_3/src/utils\n    end\n    if test -d $workspace_3/src\n        set -a dirnext $workspace_3/src\n    end\n    set -gx dirnext $dirnext\nend\n"
    }
  }
}

onDocumentSymbols
onDefinition
open_terminal_and_copy_dir_history
onDefinition
open_terminal_and_copy_dir_history
[FishLsp.onDidOpenTextDocument()]
{
  "params": {
    "textDocument": {
      "uri": "file:///home/ndonfris/.config/fish/functions/open_terminal_and_copy_dir_history.fish",
      "languageId": "fish",
      "version": 1,
      "text": "function open_terminal_and_copy_dir_history \n    set -l cmd \"fish -C 'set -gx dirprev $dirprev; set -gx dirnext $dirnext'\"\n    switch $TERM\n        case 'tilix'\n            $TERMINAL --command $cmd\n        case 'gnome-terminal'\n            $TERMINAL --command $cmd\n        case 'terminator'\n            $TERMINAL --command $cmd\n        case '*'\n            $TERMINAL --command $cmd\n    end\nend\n\n"
    }

[FishLsp.onDidOpenTextDocument()]
{
  "params": {
    "textDocument": {
      "uri": "file:///home/ndonfris/.config/fish/functions/set_dir_locations.fish",
      "languageId": "fish",
      "version": 1,
      "text": "function set_dir_locations\n    set -l dir_location $PWD;\n    if test -n $argv\n        switch \"$argv\"\n            case \"e\" \"edit\"\n                nvim $funcs/set_dir_locations.fish\n            case \"h\" \"help\"\n                echo \"set_dir_locations - set directory locations for current session\"\n\n    else \n    end\n\n\nend\n\n\n\nfunction __set_dir_location_helper\n    switch \"$PWD\"\n        case $NVIM_PATH\n            set -a -gx dirnext $NVIM_PATH/ftplugin $NVIM_PATH/lua/completions $NVIM_PATH/lua/user $NVIM_PATH/lua\n        case $FISH_PATH\n            set -a -gx dirnext $FISH_PATH/completions $FISH_PATH/scripts $FISH_PATH/functions\n        case $CONFIG_PATH\n            set -a -gx dirnext $FISH_PATH $NVIM_PATH\n        case $workspace_3\n            set -a -gx dirnext $workspace_3/src/utils\n            __open_or_jump_to_argv \"$workspace_3\"\n        case \\*\n            if test -n $argv\n                echo \"ERROR in set_dir_location\"\n                echo \"No directory found for $argv\"\n            else\n                set -l recent_reps (ls --timesort --directory-only $repos/*/ | head -n 2)\n            end\n        case ws_2 ts\n            __open_or_jump_to_argv \"$tsplayground\"\n        case edit\n            nvim $FISH_PATH/functions/jump_location.fish $FISH_PATH/config.fish\n        case \\*\n            echo -e \"\\tInvalid location: '$location'\\n\"\n            echo -e \"\\tsee $FISH_PATH/functions/jump_location.fish or pass option 'edit' to open in \\$EDITOR.\\n\"\n            echo -e \"\\tUsage: jump_location [n|f|c|r|ws_1|ws_2|ws_3|ts|*]\\n\"\n            return 0\n    end\n\nend\n\n\n"
    }
  }
}

    "textDocument": {
      "uri": "file:///home/ndonfris/.config/fish/functions/set_dir_locations.fish",
      "languageId": "fish",
      "version": 1,
      "text": "function set_dir_locations\n    set -l dir_location $PWD;\n    if test -z $argv\n        switch \"$argv\"\n            case \"e\" \"edit\"\n                nvim $funcs/set_dir_locations.fish\n            case \\*\n                echo 'set_dir_locations - set directory locations for current \\$PWD'\n                echo 'Usage: set_dir_locations [e|edit]'\n        end\n        return 0\n    else \n        __set_dir_location_helper $PWD\n    end\nend\n\n\n\nfunction __set_dir_location_helper --argument-names path\n    switch \"$path\"\n        case $NVIM_PATH\n            set -a -gx dirnext $NVIM_PATH/ftplugin $NVIM_PATH/completions $NVIM_PATH/lua/user $NVIM_PATH/lua\n        case $FISH_PATH\n            set -a -gx dirnext $FISH_PATH/completions $FISH_PATH/scripts $FISH_PATH/functions\n        case $CONFIG_PATH\n            set -a -gx dirnext $FISH_PATH $NVIM_PATH\n        case $workspace_3\n            set -a -gx dirnext $workspace_3/src/utils\n        case \\*\n            if test -n $argv\n                echo \"ERROR in set_dir_locations\"\n                echo \"No directory found for $argv\"\n            else\n                set -l recent_reps (ls --timesort --directory-only $repos/*/ | head -n 2)\n            end\n    end\n\nend\n\n\n"
    }
  }
}

      "text": "function set_nextdir\n    switch \"$argv\"\n        case \"n\" \"nvim\" \"$NVIM_PATH\"\n            set -a -gx dirnext $NVIM_PATH/ftplugin $NVIM_PATH/lua/completion $NVIM_PATH/lua/user $NVIM_PATH/lua\n        case \"f\" \"fish\" \"$FISH_PATH\"\n            set -a -gx dirnext $FISH_PATH/completions $FISH_PATH/scripts $FISH_PATH/functions\n        case \"c\" \"config\" \"$CONFIG_PATH\"\n            set -a -gx dirnext $FISH_PATH $NVIM_PATH\n        case \"1\" \"repos\" \"$workspace_1\"\n            set -a -gx dirnext (ls --timesort --directory-only $repos/*/ | head -n 2)\n        case \"2\" \"tsplayground\" \"$workspace_1\"\n            set -gx dirnext $repos\n        case \"3\" \"fish-lsp\" \"$workspace_3\"\n            set -a -gx dirnext $workspace_3/src/diagnostics\n            set -a -gx dirnext $workspace_3/src/utils\n            set -a -gx dirnext $workspace_3/src\n        case \"clear\"\n            set -e -gx dirnext\n        case \\*\n            set -l dirs (count (fd --type d --full-path \"$PWD\"))\n            if test $dirs -gt 0\n                set -a -gx dirnext (fd --type d --full-path \"$PWD\" | head -n 2)\n            else \n                echo \"unknown directory: $PWD\"\n                echo \"unknown option: $argv\"\n            end\n    end\nend\n\n\n\n\n\n"
    }
  }
}

      "text": "# called in jump_location\nfunction set_dirnext\n    switch \"$argv\"\n        case \"n\" \"nvim\" \"$NVIM_PATH\"\n            set -a -gx dirnext $NVIM_PATH/ftplugin $NVIM_PATH/lua/completion $NVIM_PATH/lua/user $NVIM_PATH/lua\n        case \"f\" \"fish\" \"$FISH_PATH\"\n            set -a -gx dirnext $FISH_PATH/completions $FISH_PATH/scripts $FISH_PATH/functions\n        case \"c\" \"config\" \"$CONFIG_PATH\"\n            set -a -gx dirnext $FISH_PATH $NVIM_PATH\n        case \"1\" \"repos\" \"$workspace_1\"\n            set -a -gx dirnext (ls --timesort --directory-only $repos/*/ | head -n 2)\n        case \"2\" \"tsplayground\" \"$workspace_1\"\n            set -gx dirnext $repos\n        case \"3\" \"fish-lsp\" \"$workspace_3\"\n            set -a -gx dirnext $workspace_3/src\n            set -a -gx dirnext $workspace_3/src/diagnostics\n            set -a -gx dirnext $workspace_3/src/utils\n            set --prepend -gx dirnext $workspace_3/fish_files\n        case \"clear\"\n            set -e -gx dirnext\n        case \\*\n            set -l dirs (count (fd --type d --full-path \"$PWD\"))\n            if test $dirs -gt 0\n                set -a -gx dirnext (fd --type d --full-path \"$PWD\" | head -n 2)\n            else \n                echo \"unknown directory: $PWD\"\n                echo \"unknown option: $argv\"\n            end\n    end\nend\n\n\n\n\n\n"
    }
  }

      "text": "function test_fish_lsp --argument-names file --description \"Check a file for syntax errors\"\n    echo \"$file\"\n    lso\n    fzf-local-node_modules\nend\n\n## this is a comment\nfunction __test_small\n    if string match --regex '^(\\w{10}).fish' -- \"$argv\"\n        echo matched | string pad -c ' '\n    end\n    string match --regex '[[:alnum:]]' \"$argv\"\n\n    # padding a stirng\n    string pad --char \" \" \"$argv\"\n    set_color --background black white\n    set -l variable_name \"v a\"\n    whatis -? --config-file --help --regex \"*\"\n    set -l variable_name (string split0 --fields 1 --right --max 4 '\\t' \"$argv\")\n    string pad --width 10 --char \" \" \"$argv\"\n    set -l variable_name \"value u\"\n    if test -n \"$variable_name\"\n        echo \"$variable_name is not empty\"\n    end\n\n    for i in $variable_name\n        echo $i\n    end\n\n    for i in $variable_name\n        echo $i\n    end\nend\n\nset -l file \"$argv\"\ntest_fish_lsp $file\n\n# implement Algorithm Implementation/Strings/Levenshtein distance\nfunction pass_func\n    set -U asdf g\nend\n\nfunction pass_func\n    echo $argv\nend\n"
    }

      "text": "function test_fish_lsp --argument-names file --description \"Check a file for syntax errors\"\n    echo \"$file\"\n    lso\n    return 0; or\n    fzf-local-node_modules\n    and \nend\n\n## this is a comment\nfunction __test_small\n    if string match --regex '^(\\w{10}).fish' -- \"$argv\"\n        echo matched | string pad -c ' '\n    end\n    string match --regex '[[:alnum:]]' \"$argv\"\n\n    # padding a stirng\n    string pad --char \" \" \"$argv\"\n    set_color --background black white\n    set -l variable_name \"v a\"\n    whatis -? --config-file --help --regex \"*\"\n    set -l variable_name (string split0 --fields 1 --right --max 4 '\\t' \"$argv\")\n    string pad --width 10 --char \" \" \"$argv\"\n    set -l variable_name \"value u\"\n    if test -n \"$variable_name\"\n        echo \"$variable_name is not empty\"\n    end\n\n    for i in $variable_name\n        echo $i\n        return\n    end\n    set -U asdf g\n\n\n    for i in $variable_name\n        echo $i\n    end\nend\n\nset -l file \"$argv\"\ntest_fish_lsp $file\n\n# implement Algorithm Implementation/Strings/Levenshtein distance\nfunction pass_func\n    set -U asdf g\nend\n\nfunction pass_func\n    echo $argv\nend\n"
    }

  "params": {

      "uri": "file:///home/ndonfris/.config/fish/functions/jump_location.fish",
      "languageId": "fish",
      "version": 1,
      "text": "function jump_location --argument-names location\n    switch \"$location\"\n        case n\n            set_dirnext 'n'; __open_or_jump_to_argv $NVIM_PATH; set_dirnext 'n'\n        case f\n            set_dirnext 'f'; __open_or_jump_to_argv \"$FISH_PATH\"; set_dirnext 'f'\n        case c\n            set_dirnext 'c';__open_or_jump_to_argv \"$CONFIG_PATH\"; set_dirnext 'c'\n        case r\n            gt r\n        case ws_1 \"1\"\n            #set -l recent_reps (ls --timesort --directory-only $repos/*/ | head -n 2)\n            set_dirnext \"1\"\n            __open_or_jump_to_argv \"$repos\"\n            set_dirnext \"1\"\n        case ws_2 ts \"2\"\n            set_dirnext \"2\"\n            __open_or_jump_to_argv \"$tsplayground\"\n
